discussion.content:
Answer D is incorrect. You can use Do-while to print an array in reverse order. Example:

public static void main(String[] args) {
 int[] array = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
 int index = array.length - 1;
 do {
 System.out.println(array[index]);
 index--;
 } while (index >= 0);
 }

